Location.$comment: The location within the property of the keysafe

Code.$comment: If the keysafe is code accessed, this is the access code

ID.$comment: The actual reference number or string used to identify a particular entity in a system or process.

Description.$comment: An optional description for the reference, or more detail about this reference or who has allocated the reference. For example, this can be used to specify that this reference is a bar code attached to some physical component.

AllocatedBy.$comment: An identifier of the organization and/or system that allocated this identifier - this could be the name of the organization and/or system or something that identifies the specific instance of a system or database where the ID originated.

DescriptionOfWork.$comment:
A written or verbal account, representation, or explanation of the problem, incident or situation to be corrected or resolved

Description of work either from SOR standard coding or private code

EstimatedLaborHours.$comment: Projected time in effort to complete the work, expressed in hours

PriorityCode.$comment: Specific code describing the importance or urgency of the work request or work order

RequiredCompletionDateTime.$comment: Time, Day, Month and Year of when the work activity specified in the Work Order is to be completed

WorkClassDescription.$comment: The description associated with the Work Class code

WorkClassCode.$comment: A code identifying the classification of work or service requested

items.$comment: A code that identifies the sub-type of classification of work or service

WorkClassSubTypeDescription.$comment: The description associated with the Work Class subtype

WorkType.$comment: Day to day, void, crime ect

ParkingArrangements.$comment: Any specific instructions regarding where or where not to park for the operatives when visiting the site/property/unit.

Code.$comment: The standard code for this trade

CustomCode.$comment: In addition to the standard code, a custom code may also be included where more detail than is available in the standard codes is required.

CustomName.$comment: Where a custom code is provided, the name of the trade may also be specified

M3NHFSORCode.$comment: A standard SOR code from the M3/NHF Schedule of Rates

CustomCode.$comment: If this is not a standard code (e.g. from a schedule), provide the custom code here

CustomName.$comment: If this is not a standard code (e.g. from a schedule), provide the name for this custom code here

items.$comment: The quantity of a commodity to which the expenditure or revenue refers

UnitOfMeasurementCode.$comment: Code defining the units of measurement.

ServiceChargeSubject.$comment: The classification of this work element according to the underlying service charge type that the associated costs will be attributed to (prior to any apportionment to tenants)

ContainsCapitalWork.$comment: True if this work element include work that may be capitalized

Type.$comment: Specifies the nature of the dependency between items - for example the dependent item cannot start until the item it depends on is complete.

Months.$comment: The number of complete months in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the number of months, before any other duration attributes.

Weeks.$comment: The number of complete weeks in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the months, then the weeks, before any other duration attributes.

Days.$comment: The number of complete days in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the months, then weeks, then days, before any other duration attributes.

Hours.$comment: The number of complete hours in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the months, then weeks, then days, then hours, before any other duration attributes.

LocationOfRepair.$comment: Description of where in the unit the work is to be undertaken

Description.$comment: Narrative description of how to access the relevant parts of the site, property and/or unit.

Comments.$comment: Specific details related to this alert - for example what specifically to be aware of, or sensible precautions to take.

Type.$comment: This provides the specific type of alert that is being flagged, e.g. 'don't visit alone'. NOTE: These alert types and associated comments must not be repeated verbatim on an operatives work order for privacy reasons. Only the information that is essential to the performance of the operatives work should be included, which may be  abstracted or summarized from the details found in the AlertRegardingPerson entity.

Comments.$comment: Specific details related to this alert - for example what specifically to be aware of, sensible precautions to take, or what the specific gender restrictions are.

Filename.$comment: The file system name of the file that is attached - used as the default or suggested name if the file is 'saved'.

AsOfDate.$comment: The last date for which the information in the attachment has been verified to be current. Also the effective date, for example the date a photograph was taken.

CreationDateTime.$comment: Date and time a document or attachment was created

URI.$comment: If the attachment is available via a link, the uniform resource identifier (URI) of the attachment. This may be a public link, or a private link to which the recipient has access.

Title.$comment: Title or caption for the attached file or document

EmbeddedFileBinaryObject.$comment: An electronic representation of the attachment encoded into text using Base64 content encoding. For more details on this encoding, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64

Description.$comment: A description of the contents of the attached file or document to help a reader establish if this is the correct file before opening

CopyrightNotices.$comment: Text description of any legal or copyright notices that may apply to the file in question

DateReported.$comment: The date and time the service request was made by the customer that gave rise to this work order, which may be earlier than the date raised if there was any delay between the customer report and issuing this work order (for example if there was a backlog processing emails).

Postbox.$comment: A post office box number or a numbered post box in a post office assigned to a person or organization where letters for them are kept until called for, used as part of an address.

Room.$comment: identifies the room, suite or apartment as part of an address.

Department.$comment:
An addressable department of an organization. E.g. 'Accounts Payable'

Where a department is used to identify the delivery point, the name of the department

Floor.$comment: To identify, by name or number, of the floor in a building, as part of an address.

Plot.$comment: A textual description of a small piece of land on which this address is located.

BuildingNumber.$comment: The number of a building or house on a street of this address.

BuildingName.$comment: The name of the building or house on a street of this address

ComplexName.$comment: Where the address is within a complex, scheme or site, the name of the complex

StreetName.$comment: Name of a street or thoroughfare

CityName.$comment: The name of the city, town or village of this address.

Country.$comment:
To provide country information related to this address.

The country of the address (not the country code)

items.$comment: Where the address cannot be separated into the explicit fields, use this as the generic 'address lines' for the address

Type.$comment: Optional name of this address to distinguish it from other address attached to the same entity

PostalCode.$comment: The identifier for one or more properties according to the postal service of that country; a group of letters and/or numbers added to the postal address to assist in the sorting of mail. E.g. UK postcode or US zip code
